Newtonsoft.Json 📦 Parameterized Constructor
This test is focused on confirming/denying whether or not a model without a parameterless constructor will deserialize without throwing an exception using Newtonsoft defaults.

Removed advent of code.
The advent of code problems will be tackled as part of this repo when time permits, but through a separate test project. Given that only the first part of the first problem for 2023 was solved, I'm okay scrapping the entire setup for it until I have time to move on it again.
Added parameterized constructor test for NSJSON.

Added null input handling to reverse.
The reverse function previously didn't handle null values gracefully and would just throw null reference exceptions. By throwing an ArgumentNullException instead, the function will now alert consumers directly to the null input instead of misleading them.
